&gt;&gt; Ah.

00:45:54.200 --> 00:45:54.800
&gt;&gt; You learn language
in bed [laughter].

00:45:56.200 --> 00:45:57.266
&gt;&gt; Okay. I'll be quick
let's say it's January 7

00:45:58.200 --> 00:46:00.600
and if you aren't finishing up a
book from the year before or is it

00:46:00.200 --> 00:46:02.866
or you are not taking a sabbatical
what is it are you thinking of ideas

00:46:02.200 --> 00:46:02.800
for the book you will
start the next day

00:46:04.200 --> 00:46:05.793
or by then you've already begun
the idea or whatever in your head.

00:46:06.940 --> 00:46:10.206
&gt;&gt; Well by January 7th I'm
a wreck because I think

00:46:11.220 --> 00:46:12.180
that I know what I'm going
to write but I don't--

00:46:13.460 --> 00:46:17.326
I am not sure and it has
happened more than once that I sit

00:46:17.490 --> 00:46:17.783
with one idea and I end up writing
something totally different.

00:46:21.330 --> 00:46:25.130
The only thing I know is that
I will have my casita clean.

00:46:25.940 --> 00:46:26.960
I will have taken out everything
that is not related to the book

00:46:29.120 --> 00:46:32.920
that I am going to write and
I have all my research ready.

00:46:33.350 --> 00:46:37.216
I light candles I put fresh
flowers, I make time, you know.

00:46:37.990 --> 00:46:38.706
I procrastinate as much as
possible but then there is a moment

00:46:41.340 --> 00:46:41.630
when I have to sit down in front of
the computer and then I breathe in

00:46:45.650 --> 00:46:45.726
and breathe out and write
a sentence that comes

00:46:48.640 --> 00:46:50.773
from the womb not from the mind.

00:46:51.440 --> 00:46:55.173
And that first sentence usually
is like a door that opens

00:46:55.650 --> 00:46:59.516
into a dark space that is the
story that I still don't know

00:47:00.310 --> 00:47:04.643
and I will go day by day, hour by
hour, word by word investigating

00:47:06.380 --> 00:47:07.130
in that darkness until I find
the characters and the story

00:47:09.430 --> 00:47:11.363
and it's a very slow process.

00:47:11.460 --> 00:47:11.493
The first two or three weeks are
terrible because I am not sure

00:47:15.560 --> 00:47:15.830
of what I'm doing and I
have not found the voice.

00:47:18.490 --> 00:47:20.823
But once the voice comes, the voice

00:47:21.260 --> 00:47:25.593
from the island beneath the sea
is the voice of Zarite, the slave.

00:47:27.070 --> 00:47:31.470
When I saw the slave and I heard
her voice, wow, the book was done.

00:47:31.940 --> 00:47:33.273
Thank you very much.

00:47:33.940 --> 00:47:35.080
&gt;&gt; Muchos gracias.

00:47:34.000 --> 00:47:35.000


